        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-red-200 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <p class="text-2xl font-black text-red-600 mb-2">Hidden Insurance Information</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Insurance list buried on contact page = patients don't know if they can afford = call elsewhere. 73% need insurance info before booking. Visible = can afford = will call. <span class="font-black text-red-600">Fix:</span> "We accept Blue Cross, Aetna, Cigna, Medicare" prominently on hero and homepage. Patients need to know insurance is accepted immediately. Hidden = can't afford = skip practice.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-red-200 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <p class="text-2xl font-black text-red-600 mb-2">No Patient Reviews</p>
