        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-red-200 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <p class="text-2xl font-black text-red-600 mb-2">"Call to Schedule" Only</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Phone-only booking = friction = abandonment. 73% prefer online scheduling. Busy patients want convenience = book online = show up. <span class="font-black text-red-600">Fix:</span> Online appointment request form with HIPAA-compliant data handling. Name, contact, preferred dates, reason for visit. Auto-confirm receipt. Easy = they schedule = reduced staff time = more appointments.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-red-200 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <p class="text-2xl font-black text-red-600 mb-2">No Health Education Content</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">No health blog = invisible in search = no organic patients. 7x more patients with educational content over 12 months. Content = found in search = trust = appointments. <span class="font-black text-red-600">Fix:</span> Health blog with preventive care tips, treatment guides. Write about: flu prevention, chronic disease management, wellness advice. 300+ words per post, weekly. People searching for health info find your content, then book appointments.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-red-200 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <p class="text-2xl font-black text-red-600 mb-2">Not Mobile-Optimized</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">73% search on phones (sick child, immediate need). Non-responsive site = broken experience = call another practice. 67% leave immediately if broken on mobile. <span class="font-black text-red-600">Fix:</span> Mobile-first design. Appointment form works on phone, click-to-call buttons, insurance visible. Mobile = they search anywhere = book immediately = more new patients.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

